{"cursor":"16491","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Nucleic acid thermodynamics' is the study of how temperature affects the\nnucleic acid structure of double-stranded DNA (dsDNA). The melting temperature\n(T m) is defined as the temperature at which half of the DNA strands\nare in the random coil or single-stranded (ssDNA) state. T m depends\non the length of the DNA molecule and its specific nucleotide sequence. DNA,\nwhen in a state where its two strands are dissociated (i.e., the dsDNA molecule\nexists as two independent strands), is referred to as having been denatured by\nthe high temperature.\n","linknr":277,"url":"Nucleic_acid_hybridisation","recorded":1362890731,"links":24,"instances":["molecular_biology","molecular_biology","biochemistry"],"pdf":["http://www.pubmedcentral.gov/picrender.fcgi?artid=323600&blobtype=pdf","http://www.invitrogen.com/content/sfs/appendix/PCR_RTPCR/Primer%20Tm%20Calculations.pdf"],"categories":["DNA","Nucleic acids","Molecular biology","Biotechnology","Chemical engineering"],"headings":["Concepts","Methods for estimating melting temperatures","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/7/e/b7e00ed422db77d8353553c23cf2601a.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/5/b/b5bdf3ee29d5fd2d7faf9d2acd790a61.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/9/6/09628dd04bce24c715b3e2f9ab853917.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/e/3/d/e3dbd30c248ab9cf12043d0916819dca.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/e/5/d/e5da2c58897ee941b57f796b86c70cec.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/6/b/a6b1cfc5b34a60b35f523d13de081280.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/f/8/4f85232a0a46502ed3bb8a126133f3da.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/1/9/e/19e2c87dfcd499d96746ef27b99584a5.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/2/b/92bbde703193217f1110b0ab9c60810b.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/7/f/37f593659cc996c4991266398ba13af6.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/3d_tRNA.png/28px-3d_tRNA.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/s